					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The main reason it wouldn't work is because you'd collide with everything.  It would detect when Mario intersected with the hill in the background.  I suppose you might use this to make a Worms/Scorched Earth sort of game, where you need pixel perfect collision on varied surfaces.
<br />
<br />I would hesitate to say its only possible use it to split the screen or finding the end of vblank.  Those are its most logical and common uses, but I'm sure a creative coder could come up with other good ways to take advantage of it.  Platformer-style collision detection is probably not going to work well, though.</div>

